1
00:00:01,859 --> 00:00:05,220
Instructor: In this course, we will be using .NET 8.

2
00:00:05,220 --> 00:00:07,680
Right now, .NET 8 is in preview.

3
00:00:07,680 --> 00:00:09,990
So if you download .NET 8,

4
00:00:09,990 --> 00:00:13,200
currently preview.2 has been released.

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,270
First, you have to download the version

6
00:00:15,270 --> 00:00:16,920
based on your system.

7
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:19,980
I have downloaded Windows x64.

8
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:22,410
And once you download .NET 8,

9
00:00:22,410 --> 00:00:27,270
then you have to download Visual Studio 2022 Preview.

10
00:00:27,270 --> 00:00:31,890
You need the Preview version if you want to work with .NET 8

11
00:00:31,890 --> 00:00:33,993
because it has not been released yet.

12
00:00:35,340 --> 00:00:38,130
Preview version can be downloaded for free.

13
00:00:38,130 --> 00:00:43,130
Just go to visualstudio.microsoft.com/vs/preview.

14
00:00:45,930 --> 00:00:50,250
Make sure to install .NET 8 and Visual Studio Preview

15
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:52,950
before you proceed with the course.

16
00:00:52,950 --> 00:00:56,250
Now, if you want to follow along with .NET 7,

17
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:59,940
you can obviously do that and everything will work

18
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:04,200
other than one change that has been introduced in .NET 8,

19
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:09,200
where they have new type, for date only and time only.

20
00:01:09,450 --> 00:01:13,350
But other than that, everything will work perfectly fine

21
00:01:13,350 --> 00:01:15,303
with .NET 7 as well.

